      "writtenOn": "2026-03-12T19:01:20Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "opengrep is more mature. There are lots of rules already out there that have been created by the community which developers could build off of. That being said, ast-grep is supposed to be faster and building it from source seems much more straightforward than building opengrep. If those aspects of ast-grep are more preferable, it shouldn\u0027t be too difficult to port the bmcweb rules to ast-grep.",
      "parentUuid": "f0104391_8a488024",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 9,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 9,
        "endChar": 23
      },
      "revId": "1c0d871f95b1b60a9e869ff2918ae3b94a263826",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "80c4caf2_632efb11",
        "filename": "/COMMIT_MSG",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 9,
      "author": {
        "id": 1000153
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-03-12T19:03:44Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "ast-grep isn\u0027t integrated in build-scripts, so while we could make a comparison, why with that one specifically?  I\u0027ve used both before, and both could probably do it, opengrep is the one Davy chose (not sure of his reasons).",
      "parentUuid": "f0104391_8a488024",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 9,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 9,
        "endChar": 23
      },
      "revId": "1c0d871f95b1b60a9e869ff2918ae3b94a263826",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "71aaafe0_aed7701e",
        "filename": "/COMMIT_MSG",
        "patchSetId": 2
