      "writtenOn": "2026-03-12T19:33:32Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "My reasons for suggesting ast-grep were: popularity, stability, and easy of use of toolchain.\n\n1. Popularity: https://www.star-history.com/?repos\u003dopengrep%2Fopengrep%2Cast-grep%2Fast-grep%2Csemgrep%2Fsemgrep\u0026type\u003ddate\u0026legend\u003dtop-left\n\nast-grep seems to be more popular than opengrep.  It is less popular than semgrep, but pretty similar.  The license change of semgrep is what caused opengrep and gives me some concerns for building on top of.\n\n2. Stability: semgrep being a commercial-ish product and then opengrep becoming a fork of it doesn\u0027t give me a lot of comfort in building our infrastructure around it.\n\n3. Toolchain: Rust vs OCaml ... should self explanatory.",
      "parentUuid": "80c4caf2_632efb11",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 9,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 9,
        "endChar": 23
      },
      "revId": "1c0d871f95b1b60a9e869ff2918ae3b94a263826",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
